s reelection in 2006. Throughout, Lula of Brazil connects this charismatic leader's life to larger issues, such as the difficulty of maintaining a progressive policy in an era of globalization. Brazil's contemporary history, parallels with other developing countries and other world leaders, the conservatism of Brazilian society, and other themes provide a rich backdrop for assessing the struggles, achievements, and failures of this major figure on both the Brazilian and the world stage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPresidentszBrazilvBiography. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / General.2bisacsh  a20th century.  abiographical.  abrazil.  abrazilian history.  abrazilian politics.  abrazilian president.  achildhood.  acoming of age.  acorruption.  adictator.  adictatorship.  aelections.  aglobalization.  agrowing up.  ahard times.  alatin america.  aleadership.  alife story.  ametalworker.  amilitary.  anarrative.  apolitical.  apolitics.  apresidency.  apresident.  aprogressive politics.  aprogressive.  ascandal.  asouth america.  atrue story.  aworld leader.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026155640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093252440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520932524423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520932524/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY